{
  "_meta": {
    "version": "v0",
    "description": "Per-family pricing rules for resource-priced providers (GCP, Oracle). Each entry tells compare() how to take an upstream rate row plus a (vcpu, ram_gb) ask and synthesize a composite result with a custom-shape name and a composite citation. See ADR 0006 (decision) and ADR 0007 (parquet schema).",
    "schema": {
      "<provider>.<family>.vcpu_per_unit": "How many vCPU one priced unit covers. GCP prices per vCPU directly (1). Oracle x86 prices per OCPU = 2 vCPU (2). Oracle Ampere ARM prices per OCPU = 1 vCPU (1).",
      "<provider>.<family>.vcpu_min": "Minimum vCPU count for a valid configuration.",
      "<provider>.<family>.vcpu_max": "Maximum vCPU count.",
      "<provider>.<family>.vcpu_step": "Allowed vCPU increment (1 = any integer, 2 = even-only, etc.).",
      "<provider>.<family>.custom_name_template": "Python str.format pattern for the synthesized instance_type label. Supported placeholders: {vcpu}, {ram_gb}, {ram_mb}, {ocpu}.",
      "<provider>.<family>.taxonomy_family": "Cross-provider family slug from families.json that this flex family maps into.",
      "<provider>.<family>.notes": "Architecture context for agent prose.",
      "<provider>.<family>.ram_per_unit_gb": "{min, max} legal RAM-per-priced-unit ratio. For GCP the unit is vCPU; for Oracle Flex the unit is OCPU. compare() multiplies vcpu_per_unit through the constraint check so the user-facing ask in vCPU resolves correctly."
    },
    "v0_coverage": "GCP general-purpose (n1/n2/n2d/n4/n4a/n4d/e2/t2a/t2d), compute-optimized (c2/c2d/c3/c3d/c4/c4a/c4d), memory-optimized (m1/m2/m3/m4), storage-optimized (z3). Oracle Flex (E3/E4/E5/E6 AMD, A1/A2/A4 Ampere ARM, X9 Intel). GPU families and HPC families are out of v0 because their pricing includes a third atomic resource (GPU-hour) and we have not yet wired three-way composition."
  },
